<%# Phase 26 — 01d. Help-modal fragment.

    Rendered with `layout: false` from `Settings::Webhooks::HelpController#show`
    and swapped into the layout-level `<turbo-frame id="webhook_help_modal_frame">`
    on the user's `[help]` click. The matching frame id on both sides
    (request + response) lets Turbo replace the inner contents of the
    modal without a full navigation.

    Server-side Markdown rendering only — no JS Markdown library
    (server-rendered Markdown is the contract per the spec). The
    rendered HTML is wrapped in `.markdown-body` so the existing
    note-preview styles apply (headings, code blocks, lists, links).
    `plain: true` switches off the header-anchor + syntax-highlight
    Commonmarker plugins — the guides ship in monospace prose and
    don't need either of those decorations.

    Friendly URLs:
      `/settings/webhooks/help/slack`
      `/settings/webhooks/help/discord`
    Both 200 with this fragment. Anything else → 404 (router-level
    constraint plus controller allow-list).

    `target_external_links: true` — guides link out to Slack / Discord
    canonical docs (api.slack.com, support.discord.com, etc.) and to
    the providers' app directories. Per the pito hard rule (every link
    to an external website opens in a new tab; see `docs/design.md` →
    "External links — new tab convention") the renderer rewrites
    those anchors to carry `target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"`
    so a `[help]` click never yanks the user out of their pito
    settings tab. %>
<%# Beta 4 F3-DEEP-A — TUI revamp. Wrap the rendered Markdown guide in
    a Tui::FramedPanelComponent with a lowercase + brand-capitalized
    title (`Slack` / `Discord` brand names stay capitalized per project
    rule). A bottom-row `[close]` muted bracketed link gives the user
    an explicit exit (the modal also closes via its existing controller
    on Esc / backdrop click — this is just an in-content affordance). %>
<%
  brand = @provider.to_s == "discord" ? "Discord" : "Slack"
  panel_title = "webhook help — #{brand}"
%>
<%= turbo_frame_tag "webhook_help_modal_frame" do %>
  <%= render Tui::FramedPanelComponent.new(title: panel_title) do %>
    <div class="webhook-help-content markdown-body" data-webhook-help="<%= @provider %>">
      <%= render_markdown(@markdown, plain: true, target_external_links: true) %>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-top: 12px; padding-top: 8px; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); display: flex; justify-content: flex-start;">
      <%= render BracketedMutedLinkComponent.new(label: "close", href: "#", data: { action: "click->webhook-help-modal#close" }) %>
    </div>
  <% end %>
<% end %>
